 Oi Davi, obrigada pela conversa!

Gostaria de te convidar para a pr=C3=B3xima fase do nosso processo seletivo=
: a
entrevista chamada Business Phone Screen (BPS) para a posi=C3=A7=C3=A3o de =
Software
Engineer II - L4. Caso queira conhecer um pouco mais sobre o Frontend aqui
na Uber, segue o link do nosso =C3=BAltimo meetup
<https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3DEGHHaOgUzPU>

Essa entrevista tem como foco a resolu=C3=A7=C3=A3o de problemas, abordando=
 tanto
C=C3=B3digo (Algoritmos) quanto Design & Arquitetura (D&A). Nosso objetivo =
=C3=A9
avaliar suas habilidades de programa=C3=A7=C3=A3o e entender melhor a compl=
exidade e
o escopo dos seus projetos anteriores sob a =C3=B3tica de D&A. N=C3=A3o se =
trata de
uma an=C3=A1lise exaustiva da sua profundidade t=C3=A9cnica ou expertise em=
 design,
mas sim de uma avalia=C3=A7=C3=A3o inicial para determinar sua qualifica=C3=
=A7=C3=A3o para
seguir para as pr=C3=B3ximas entrevistas.

*Estrutura da entrevista*
~45 minutos: Codifica=C3=A7=C3=A3o
~15 minutos: Design & Arquitetura

*Linguagem de programa=C3=A7=C3=A3o*
Fica a seu crit=C3=A9rio! Escolha com sabedoria e certifique-se de estar be=
m
confort=C3=A1vel e proficiente nela.

*Como se preparar*
Temos uma p=C3=A1gina espec=C3=ADfica para prepara=C3=A7=C3=A3o, voc=C3=AA =
encontra mais informa=C3=A7=C3=B5es
aqui
<https://www.uber.com/us/en/careers/engineering-interview-guide/?nocache=3D=
true>
.
> Pratique algoritmo: se voc=C3=AA est=C3=A1 enferrujado(a) ou n=C3=A3o tem=
 familiaridade
com pair programming, vale a pena treinar antes. Resolva alguns desafios de
diferentes n=C3=ADveis de dificuldade em plataformas como LeetCode. Teste s=
eu
c=C3=B3digo continuamente e foque nos seguintes t=C3=B3picos:

   - Common data structures and algorithms (e.g., hash tables, trees,
   stacks).
   - Data structures, particularly the ones used most often (e.g., arrays,
   stacks (or queues), hash tables, trees, graphs, and heaps).
   - Runtime analysis (Big-O notation) and optimization techniques.
   - Problem-solving approaches: Practice solving scenarios common in
   large-scale tech companies.

*Materiais de estudo*


   - Graphos Mock Interview + Tips
   <https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3DuTnJoAIZoF0>
   - V=C3=ADdeo Mock interview
   <https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3DYBKfvoUu5LY&feature=3Dyoutu.be>
   - V=C3=ADdeo Mock interview 2 <https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3DxxAnIoI=
xWGM>
   - Coding interview: dicas para o processo seletivo de Engenharia da Uber
   <https://www.uber.com/pt-BR/blog/coding-interview-dicas-para-o-processo-=
seletivo-de-engenharia-da-uber/>



*EXTRA* Exerc=C3=ADcios no Leet Code para praticar c=C3=B3digo:


   - Number of Provinces
   <https://leetcode.com/problems/number-of-provinces/description/>
   - House Robber III
   <https://leetcode.com/problems/house-robber-iii/description/>
   - Number of Enclaves
   <https://leetcode.com/problems/number-of-enclaves/description/>
   - Longest Consecutive Sequence
   <https://leetcode.com/problems/longest-consecutive-sequence/description/=
>


*Durante a entrevista*

   - Be ready to write and explain your solution in a live coding
   environment.
   - Ask clarifying questions: Analyze the problem and make sure that you
   fully understand it before jumping in. It=E2=80=99s OK to ask clarifying=
 questions
   during the interview to make sure you understand the exact problem you a=
re
   trying to solve. Also, breaking down the problem into smaller pieces can=
 be
   helpful.
   - Account for edge cases: Think through and address edge cases to show
   thorough problem analysis. One technique to write a better solution is t=
o
   consider what you would catch if you were code reviewing your code.
   - Communicate your thought process: Walk the interviewer through your
   reasoning as you solve the problem. Before implementing, discuss your
   proposed solution to ensure alignment.
   - Keep things simple: If you find the solution getting excessively
   complex, step back and ask if there=E2=80=99s a simpler way to solve it.=
 It may
   also be helpful to write everything out so you can see insights and bugs
   faster and make fewer mistakes.
   - Test and debug: Continuously test your code and handle exceptions to
   confirm your solution works.
   - Write clear, readable code: Use meaningful variable names and keep
   formatting consistent for easy understanding.
   - Engage with follow-up questions: Be prepared to dive deeper into your
   solution and discuss alternative approaches or improvements.


   - Refresh yourself on Design & Architecture:
      - Be prepared to talk about a project that highlights the complexity
      and scope of your role, including architectural components and design
      decision-making.
      - Be ready to discuss trade-offs: Why was one technology chosen over
      another? What was the reasoning behind key decisions?
   - Other:
      - Reflect on impact: Think about the scope and results of your past
      roles and how they relate to solving problems at Uber.
      - Review the job description: Identify relevant experiences from your
      background and prepare to showcase them during the interview.
      - Prepare questions: Consider any role-specific or team-related
      questions to ask your interviewer.


E a dica mais importante: estudar faz toda a diferen=C3=A7a! Acreditamos qu=
e
esse material ser=C3=A1 =C3=BAtil para sua prepara=C3=A7=C3=A3o, e estamos =
torcendo para que
voc=C3=AA tenha um =C3=B3timo desempenho!

Em breve, o time de Talent Coordinators entrar=C3=A1 em contato por e-mail =
para
confirmar sua disponibilidade, al=C3=A9m de compartilhar o nome de quem vai=
 te
entrevistar, o link do Zoom e o link do exerc=C3=ADcio. Combinado?

Caso tenha alguma d=C3=BAvida, =C3=A9 s=C3=B3 me avisar!
Atenciosamente,

